title: Feed the Giant Oyster

description: The totem top is found by searching the rubble north of the larger of the two ruins on the north-east portion of the island.

description: There are a total of 60 Ancient Zygomites scattered across Anachronia. They're dug into the ground and disguised as flowers.

description: Building the rope rack requires a Construction level of 24, 3 oak planks and 5 ropes.

title: Obtain a Long or Curved bone

description: Deliver five crates of supplies from Captain Denulth to the Ambush Commander upon completion of the Death Plateau quest. Captain Denulth can be found slightly north east of Burthorpe Lodestone. The commander is stationed at the top of the Death Plateau.

title: Obtain an Imp repellent
description: The repellent can be obtained from Elnock Inquisitor in Puro-Puro by trading him three Baby, two Young and one Gourmet Impling(s). Alternatively, it can be made by combining any flower with sieved anchovy paste in an empty vial. A Sieve can be obtained from the Rimmington Chemist.

title: Obtain a uniquely coloured Tribal mask, wear it, and kill another broodoo victim with a mask of that colour
description: The masks are obtained by killing broodoo victims during the Tai Bwo Wannai clean-up activity. Using the Broodoo victims weakness results in the mask being impossible to obtain.

title: Obtain the Salve amulet (e)
description: The Salve Amulet is obtained after the Haunted Mine quest. To enchant the amulet, you must traverse the Lair of Tarn Razolor and defeat Tarn and his pack of Terror Dogs (requiring a Slayer level of 40 to harm) in the end.

title: Obtain a set of Shade robes
description: The robes are dropped by level 61 Shades located at the entrance to the last level of the Stronghold of Security.

title: Construct and add 3 unique species to the Menagerie of your Player-owned House
description: Building the Oak pet house and Oak pet feeder require you to own a house and a Construction level of 37.

title: Buy a chapel and construct an altar in your Player-Owned House
description: Buying the chapel requires a Construction level of 45 and costs 50k gp. The altar can be constructed using 4 Oak planks.

title: Find the Postcat

title: Unlock the Eagle transport system

description: Obtaining the staff requires the caper 'Lost Her Marbles' to be completed. A Thieving level of 41 is needed for this.

title: Create 25 Energy potions (3)
description: Energy potions can be made by mixing a clean Harralander with chocolate dust in a vial of water. This requires a Herblore level of 26.

title: Create 75 Prayer potions (3)
description: Prayer potions can be made by mixing a clean Ranarr with snape grass in a vial of water. This requires a Herblore level of 38.

title: Create 75 Super strength potions (3)
description: Super strength potions can be made by mixing a clean Kwuarm and a limpwurt root in a vial of water. This requires a Herblore of 55.

title: Create 10 Spirit kalphite pouches
description: Spirit kalphites are created by using a Summoning pouch on a Summoning obelisk with 51 spirit shards, a blue charm, a potato cactus and a Summoning level of 25.

title: Create 10 Beaver pouches
description: Beavers are created by using a Summoning pouch on a Summoning obelisk, with a green charm, 72 spirit shards, 1 willow log, and a Summoning level of 33.

title: Create 10 Magpie pouches
description: Magpies are created by using a Summoning pouch on a Summoning obelisk, with a green charm, 88 spirit shards, a gold ring and a Summoning level of 47.

title: Successfully cook 200 Rainbow fish
description: A Fishing level of 38 and a Cooking level of 35 are required.

title: Successfully cook 300 Bass
description: A Fishing level of 46 and a Cooking level of 43 are required.

title: Obtain a Cobalt chinchompa (unchecked) for your Player-Owned Farm
description: The unchecked Cobalt chinchompa can be found at a 1/1500 checked traps rate. They require level 27 Hunter to catch, the completion of the Player Owned Farm tutorial, and they can be found in the Tree Gnome Stronghold hunter area.

title: Obtain a Viridian chinchompa (unchecked) for your Player-Owned Farm
description: The unchecked Viridian chinchompa can be found at a 1/1500 checked traps rate. They require level 46 Hunter to catch, and can be found in the Port Phasmatys hunter area.

title: Obtain a Spotted cape
description: The cape can be obtained by bringing 2 Spotted kebbit furs to the Fancy Dress Shop in south-east Varrock. The furs require a Hunter level of 43 to obtain.

title: Obtain a Magical butterfly net
description: The butterfly net can be obtained from Elnock Inquisitor in Puro-Puro by trading him three Gourmet, two Earth and an Essence impling(s). Catching an Essence impling requires a Hunter level of 42.

title: Obtain a unique from TzHaar
description: One unique from Mej, 3 uniques from Xil, the cape is dropped by all and the Ket-Om and the shield are dropped by the Xil and Ket.

title: Unlock the 3rd tier of reputation with the Imperial district of Menaphos
description: Reputation can be obtained through various skilling activities in Menaphos; furthermore, squashing Corrupted scarabs and using the Soul Obelisk awards large quantities of reputation, too.

description: All types of Ghosts and ghost-like creatures drop the uniques. These include the Ghost hunter equipment, the Deployable herb burner, the Ectoplasmator and the Cremation ability.

title: Obtain a Long or Curved bone
description: The bones are dropped from all big bones droppers. They have a drop rate of 1/400 and 1/5000 respectively.

title: Assist the citizens of Morton for good
description: Deliver the Diary of Herbi Flax, found on the shelves in the southwestern part of Morton, to the Apothecary in Varrock; upon completion it is in your POH Bookcase. Secondly, cure Razmire Keelgan and Ulsquire Shauncy permanently of their affliction using a Serum 208. This requires a Herblore level of 15.

title: Loot the chest in Klenters Pyramid
description: Klenters Pyramid is found south of Pyramid Plunder in Sophanem. Access to the pyramid requires partial completion of the Itchlarins Little Helper quest.

title: Raid the Demon throne room
description: Claim the gems from the Demon Throne found below Uzer. This requires partial completion of the Golem quest.

title: Participate in the Dorgesh-Kaan trading minigame
description: Speak to Lurgon in the Dorgesh-Kaan marketplace to start. Completion of the Death to the Dorgeshuun quest is required to access Dorgesh-Kaan.

title: Fully complete the Death of Chivalry quest
description: Full completion of the quest requires 7 post-quest rewards to be obtained. To do this, a Farming level of 7, a Strength level of 80 and a Prayer level of 65 is required. Refer to the wiki for further details.

title: School a Natural Historian on Muspah anatomy
description: Speak to the Natural Historian in the Rellekka Hunter area and answer his questions regarding the Muspah upon completion of the Tale of the Muspah quest.

title: Fully complete the Gower quest
description: There are 2 Rewards to claim post-quest. Two bobblehead pets, and the three exp lamps, the latter requiring level 50 in all skills.

title: Defeat the Phoenix
description: The Phoenix Lair can be found south west of Piscatoris. A Firemaking level of 55, a Crafting level of 52, a Fletching level of 53 and a Slayer level of 51 is required for completion of In Pyre Need and fighting the Phoenix.

title: Scavenge the Meiyerditch Laboratories for Bloodstained Treasure
description: During or upon completion of the Legacy of Seergaze quest, loot the runes from the Broken Rune Case in the Meiyerditch Laboratories. Secondly, loot the corpse next to the Blood Altar ruins.

title: Super Duper Secret Task #19
description: Be a gentle-task-man and pay Vanligga Gastfrihet's taxes during or upon completion of the Fremennik Isles quest.

title: Purchase an Ancient Staff from Eblis
description: Eblis can be found at the Bandit Camp Lodestone.

title: Unlock the ability to sell noted artefacts
description: Complete a Job for Simon Templeton upon completion of the Dealing with Scabaras quest to unlock the ability to trade noted artefacts. Simon Templeton can be found at the Agility Pyramid in the Kharidian Desert.

title: Super Duper Secret Task #20
description: Listen to The Epic of Bakulla

title: Restore the Fairy Ring in the Ancient Cavern
description: To restore the Fairy ring, 5 Bittercap mushrooms must be planted in the wrecked ring. The Ancient Caverns require partial completion of Otto Godblesseds barbarian training.

title: Free the Rogue trader
description: Enter the Spirit Realm at the Rogues Castle upon completion of the Summers End quest, and set the Rogue Trader free. The trader is locked up in a cell at the back of the castle.

title: Super Duper Secret Task #21
description: There are 22 treasures scattered throughout Gielinor upon completion of the Meeting- and Making History quests. Find them.

title: Unlock the ability to make Trollheim tablets
description: Give a Miners Diary, which can be obtained from the Runvastr located in east Keldagrim, to the Wise Old Man.

title: Obtain a unique piece of Splitbark equipment
description: The gear can be obtained by providing Wizard Jalarast with Bark and Fine Cloth, A Crafting and Runecrafting level of 40 is required for the weapons. Lastly, they can be obtained from Ravenous Ghouls.

title: Obtain a unique piece of Splitbark equipment

title: Unlock the Willow campfire boost at War's Retreat
description: A total of 1000 Marks of War and 1000 Willow logs are required to unlock the enhanced effects of the bonfire. If you do not already have the Marks of War, you are allowed to kill the boss you've most recently had a task for, until you have the required marks.

title: Unlock the Maple campfire boost at War's Retreat
description: A total of 1000 Marks of War and 1000 Maple logs are required to unlock the enhanced effects of the bonfire. If you do not already have the Marks of War, you are allowed to kill the boss you've most recently had a task for, until you have the required marks.

title: Unlock the Yew campfire boost at War's Retreat
description: A total of 1000 Marks of War and 1000 Yew logs are required to unlock the enhanced effects of the bonfire. If you do not already have the Marks of War, you are allowed to kill the boss you've most recently had a task for, until you have the required marks.

title: Throw a total of 100K GP into the Whirlpool at the Deep Sea Fishing Hub for good RNG
description: A Fishing level of 68 is required to access the Hub. Events are called in the WhirlpoolDnD friends chat. If there is no Whirlpool available, you are allowed to Fish at the Deep sea fishing hub until one is available.

title: Hand in one of each of the 4 Sqirk juices to Osman in one go
description: Sqirk juices can be obtained from Sorcerer's Garden, and can then be handed in to either Osman or Emir Ali Mirza who are both found in the Al Kharid Palace. A Thieving level of 65 is required to access all 4 gardens.

title: Super Duper Secret Task #31
description: Use the random option on the NPC Contact spell and try and figure out if it's a bad time to call

title: Unlock all Charter ship routes
description: In order to unlock all routes, the Jack of Spades, Cabin Fever, As a First Resort, Monkey Madness and Regicide quests must be completed.

title: Fill Dave's Spellbook with 100 of each teleport tablet
description: Obtaining the book requires completion of the Evil Dave's Big Day Out quest. Making the tabs requires a Construction level of 67 as well as completion of the Watchtower and Biohazard quests.

title: Unlock improved experience gains for the Circus D&D
description: Completion of Back to the Freezer is required to do this.

title: Unlock the Tuska Storm teleport
description: Tuska Storm teleport costs 1200 reward currency from the Anima Islands minigame.

title: Complete Sir Atcha's second Saradominist collection
description: A total of 9 artefacts must be given to Sir Atcha in the White Knight's Castle in Falador. An Archaeology level of 72 is required.

title: Complete Velucia's second Saradominist museum collection
description: A total of 9 artefacts must be given to Velucia at the Varrock Digsite. An Archaeology level of 72 is required.

title: Complete Chief Tess' Blingy Fings collection
description: A total of 5 artefacts must be given to Chief Tess in Oo'glog. An Archaeology level of 69 is required. You are allowed to hand in collections if you happen to complete them during your Arch tasks.

title: Offer the Berserker's Fury relic to the mysterious monolith
description: Dharok's Memento is made by combining a Lock of Hair and an Amulet of the Forsaken. This requires an Archaeology level of 56 and completion of Sir Atcha's first collection.

title: Super Duper Secret Task #43
description: Bring Helen the perfect cup of tea at the Archaeology campus, nothing like a nice cuppa tea!

title: Super Duper Secret Task #44
description: Enter the Warforge wearing H.A.M robes. An Archaeology level of 76 is required to access Warforge!

title: Talk to one of the ghosts in Kharid-et while wearing a full set of ghostly robes
description: The robes are obtained from the Curse of Zaros miniquest.
